main event: A GOC observer spotted a round object on November 23, 1957, above Washington Island, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 5 minutes,The object was larger than a star,The observer described the object as possibly pink in color,The object moved in a northeast direction and faded over the horizon,The jet aircraft present could not catch up to the object.
witness description: Mrs. C. B. Eaton, a 45-year-old housewife, GOC observer
